
 +-------------------------------------------------+
 | rbackup -- Yet another wrapper around duplicity |
 +-------------------------------------------------+

==> What is it
This is a python wrapper around duplicity, using LVM snapshots and desktop
notifications using notificationd (http://github.com/r3boot/notificationd).
It is made for laptops which not always have access to a private backup server.

==> Features
* Automatic detection of full/incremental backups
* Automatic configuration of configuration and ssh keys
* YAML based configuration
* LVM snapshots and cleanup
* Aborts if not running in a trusted network
* Desktop notifications

==> Usage
$ cd rbackup
$ sudo python setup.py install
$ sudo rbackup --setup
$ sudo vi /etc/rbackup/config.yaml
$ sudo rbackup
